## 🐛 Bug Report

<!-- A clear and concise description of what the bug is. -->

Lib version: 4.4.0

## Steps To Reproduce

<!-- The exact steps required to reproduce the issue, ideally with a code example -->

```javascript
const imageSustain = workbook.addImage({
    filename: 'public/sustain.png',
    extension: 'png',
});
sheet.addImage(imageSustain, 'A1:B3');
sheet.addRows(topRows);
```

## The expected behaviour:

<!-- A clear and concise description of what you expected to happen. -->

In version 4.3.0 addImage and addRows functioned such that addImage isn't adding two rows before addRows. In version 4.4.0, two rows are being created by addImage before addRows.

## Possible solution (optional, but very helpful):

```javascript
const imageSustain = workbook.addImage({
    filename: 'public/sustain.png',
    extension: 'png',
});
sheet.addRows(topRows);
sheet.addImage(imageSustain, 'A1:B3');
```
